SIMPLE: simply
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Simply
<hw>Sim"ply</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a
simple manner or state; considered in or by itself; without addition;
along; merely; solely; barely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[They] make that now good or evil, . . . which otherwise of itself
were not <qex>simply</qex> the one or the other.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Simply</qex> the thing I am⟦br⟧
Shall make me live.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1343 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Plainly; without art or subtlety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Subverting worldly strong and worldly wise⟦br⟧
By <qex>simply</qex> meek.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Weakly; foolishly.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Simulachre</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Simulacher</ent>⟦br⟧
